metadata.name: Sweeping #101
metadata.description:
Sweeping is a piece in which I explore the uses of noise fields. Using them in the most cliche way possible, but trying to make something unique out of that.

What started out as an innocent weekend project grew out to be quite the piece, which is why I am publishing it here.



Sweeping uses the GPU of your machine for its shading, which means it won't run particularly well on mobile devices. My recommended way of viewing this piece is on a PC with a dedicated GPU.

---

- Double Click to open a User Interface
- In the UI, you can toggle the paper texture and export

---

Made with p5js + webgl by Wouter Missler, 2022.

To celebrate #fxhashturnsone!

Vanilla JS + SVG
November 2022

Edition of 365

This project began as an attempt to recreate the backgrounds of some of my favourite landscape painters. However the results of this exercise merited further exploration on their own. 

In this version, 10 variegated lines (each one consisting of a hundred or so coloured rectangles) are post-processed with a little noise, resulting in sometimes diaphanous, sometimes detailed forms and 'landscapes' of the imagination.

You can animate the piece by pressing "A" or stop the animation pressing "H".
Change the speed of the animation with "1", "2" or "3".
To save a PNG file, press "P" or save an SVG by pressing "S"

WARNING: This project may not work on mobile devices and in some browsers depending on support for SVG and SVG filters. 

// PRIMARY SALES

50% to Pakistan Relief
50% to Women of Iran

metadata.name: Ceremony #100
metadata.description:
This series celebrates fxhash turning one. #fxhashturnsone

I’m so grateful for this place and have ho idea how to adequately articulate how much this platform has changed my life, but it has. A million thanks to the team. You are so appreciated as are the artists and collectors that have made this such a beautiful community. 🥂

Definitely check out “Forever” mode by tapping “F” or mouse click/tap — it will animate (you guessed it) forever and will change its layout every 365 frames, in honor of this wonderful year, and every year after. Some forever modes will “never forget” and others will fade as they progress. No idea if that’s a metaphor but it is a trait, that much I know.

All primary sales are donated to Code/Art, which is a charity that uses “…Art to Inspire Girls in Computer Science.” Read about Code/Art here: https://www.code-art.com/

Ceremony uses public domain art (which is the original, more implicit version CC0) made exclusively by women.

See fxtext article linked from the project page for a gallery of the source material and other notes.

Ceremony is also CC0, so feel free use anything here in other projects.

You can read more about CC0 here:
https://creativecommons.org/share-your-work/public-domain/cc0/

F : “Forever” mode (tap after initial render completes)
P : Pause/Play
(mouse click/tap also works to start “Forever” mode or Pause/Play)

A : Add Grain (only works when paused in “Forever” mode.)
G : Toggle Grain (resets the whole piece)
M : Toggle Matte (resets the whole piece)

S : Save Image
1 -> 6 : Set pixel density (resets the whole piece)
(Default pixel density is 1 @ 2000x2000)

If you want to start in "Forever" mode, you can append "&forever=true" to the url in the live view.
You can also add pixel density to the url by appending “&density=2” (or 3, 4, etc) to have it render at higher resolutions by default.

metadata.description:

metadata.name: Ethereal Microcosm #202
metadata.description:
An exploration of algorithmic organisms in a contained environment.

This piece is about the simulation of microscopic patterns using a high number of even tinier agents all following the same rules. Different species evolve and interact together, resulting in stabilizing patterns out of their parametric configurations. A form of artificial life.

This work is based on the paper "Characteristics of pattern formation and evolution in approximations of physarum transport networks", written by Jeff Jones and popularized in the artistic field by Sage Jenson. Some features were added to increase the visual and behavioral complexity of the system. Agents are divided into different species, with their own set of rules and interacting with their own substrate. Substrates also interact with each other and agents will mutate in contact of some of them.

NFT License
Runs properly on Chrome 97.0.4692.99
GPU intensive

Press P to pause (double tab touch devices)

metadata.name: Conspiracy Theory #112
metadata.description:
The idea is inspired by the conspiracy board.

Conspiracy theories may go so far that even people, in newspapers and books, look for clues. 
The text is from Alice in Wonderland, which is randomly selected and then words are selected to be highlighted and circled, and eventually numbers may be written next to some of them to create a network of clues.

Press ’s’ on the live mode to save the artwork.
Made with P5js.

metadata.name: TENDER Pass #815
metadata.description:
Tender is a curatorial platform and community that helps bring incredible works of generative art to discerning collectors.

Holding a TENDER Pass enables enriched benefits and experiences within the Tender ecosystem. Passholders expand their access to unique collaborations with extraordinary artists, indispensable collector tools, curatorial experiences, artwork insights, fine art prints, a thriving community, and more.

Tender is committed to stewarding the growth of generative art and amplifying the voices of artists and collectors across the entire lifecycle: from creation to collection to curation, and back again. Every Pass minted and resold directly enables Tender to continue creating the platform and experiences that serve this mission.

——

TENDER Pass features unique artwork by punevyr. While all Passes are special, a small number of randomly generated, rarified tokens will come with boosted benefits. If you have a piece with a dark background of any kind, you likely possess one of the following:

Bonus Pass
TENDER Passes with the special Bonus trait get 1 guaranteed reserve spot on all TENDER x Collab projects

Grail Pass
TENDER Passes with the special Grail trait get 2 free mints on all TENDER x Collab projects


New Passholders may access our Discord server that’s linked from our website.
For TENDER Pass benefits and up-to-date details, please visit tender.art/pass


Artwork created with p5.js

---

TENDER x punevyr
July 2022
